The paper describes a computer vision-based approach for analyzing 3D printing processes, which involves multiple-stage monocular image examination. This approach involves analyzing both the external shape of the printed object and the internal structure of its layers. The paper also discusses the use of various algorithms for analyzing the printing process, such as multi-template matching, iterative closest point algorithms, and Gaussian mixture models. Given the focus on computer vision and image analysis, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Other likely sub-categories include cs.RO (Robotics), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.GR (Graphics).
